## ğŸš© Dangers of Blind Loyalty
- Companies prioritize profit and cut even loyal staff when convenient[attached_file:1].
- Managers may exploit dependable employees for extra, often unpaid, work[attached_file:1].
- Loyalty may prevent you from pursuing better roles, stalling promotions and salary growth[attached_file:1].
- Corporate promises (promotions, hikes) are often broken or indefinitely postponed[attached_file:1].
- Oversharing career aspirations or frustrations at work can backfire due to office politics[attached_file:1].
- Letting work consume your identity leads to stress and loss of personal growth[attached_file:1].

